The paper discusses an expert system for recommending machine learning algorithms based on domain knowledge extracted from a large corpus of academic publications. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the use of word embedding representations and natural language processing techniques suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the information retrieval (cs.IR) and computational linguistics (cs.CL) sub-categories. The paper's focus on expert systems and recommendation models also suggests that it may be relevant to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the use of deep learning techniques for word embeddings suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the deep learning (cs.DL) sub-category.
